                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12706590" author="streamy" created="Wed, 6 May 2009 21:13:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Question is... what do we use?  I&apos;m thinking it&apos;s:  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;HeapSize.OBJECT + 2 * HeapSize.INT + HeapSize.BYTE_ARRAY + wordAlign(bytes.length)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12706593" author="streamy" created="Wed, 6 May 2009 21:15:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;HeapSize.BYTE_ARRAY is actually incorrect in trunk.  It is = REFERENCE, but should be 3 * REF (same as HeapSize.ARRAY).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch will fix that too, not worth another issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12706959" author="stack" created="Thu, 7 May 2009 16:11:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Regards sizes, should we file a task JIRA that we run just before release, a verification of all estimates using Ryans&apos; instrumented JVM args doohicky?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12706966" author="erikholstad@gmail.com" created="Thu, 7 May 2009 16:18:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, sounds like a good plan, just before release go over all the HeapSize class estimations and check them again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12708775" author="stack" created="Wed, 13 May 2009 06:13:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for patch Jon and Erik (I cut it from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1304&quot; title=&quot;New client server implementation of how gets and puts are handled. &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1304&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1304&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
